{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-16",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_16_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 16 - The Third Murder",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 4,
  "page_total": 6,
  "page_start_sec": 740.25,
  "page_end_sec": 986.74,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.671,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 740.25,
      "end": 741.0,
      "text": "Spade,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 741.12,
      "end": 742.42,
      "text": "wooden-faced and nimble,"
    },
    {
      "start": 742.52,
      "end": 744.78,
      "text": "sprang from his chair and caught the falling man."
    },
    {
      "start": 745.9,
      "end": 746.88,
      "text": "When Spade caught him,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 747.0,
      "end": 748.32,
      "text": "the man's mouth opened,"
    },
    {
      "start": 748.46,
      "end": 751.08,
      "text": "and a little blood spurted out and the brown-wrapped"
    },
    {
      "start": 751.2,
      "end": 753.54,
      "text": "parcel dropped from the man's hands and rolled"
    },
    {
      "start": 753.54,
      "end": 755.48,
      "text": "across the floor until the foot of the desk"
    },
    {
      "start": 755.72,
      "end": 756.22,
      "text": "stopped it."
    },
    {
      "start": 757.632,
      "end": 758.88,
      "text": "Then the man's knees bent,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 759.08,
      "end": 760.3,
      "text": "and he bent at the waist,"
    },
    {
      "start": 760.48,
      "end": 761.52,
      "text": "and his thin body became"
    },
    {
      "start": 761.66,
      "end": 763.7,
      "text": "limber inside the sheath-like overcoat,"
    },
    {
      "start": 764.04,
      "end": 766.88,
      "text": "sagging in Spade's arm so that Spade could not hold"
    },
    {
      "start": 766.88,
      "end": 767.78,
      "text": "it up from the floor."
    },
    {
      "start": 769.088,
      "end": 772.32,
      "text": "Spade lowered the man gently until he lay on the floor on his left",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 772.42,
      "end": 772.68,
      "text": "side."
    },
    {
      "start": 773.86,
      "end": 774.54,
      "text": "The man's eyes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 774.78,
      "end": 775.8,
      "text": "dark and bloodshot,"
    },
    {
      "start": 775.98,
      "end": 777.04,
      "text": "but not now mad,"
    },
    {
      "start": 777.36,
      "end": 778.92,
      "text": "were wide open and still."
    },
    {
      "start": 779.8,
      "end": 782.58,
      "text": "His mouth was open as when blood had spurted from it,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 782.62,
      "end": 784.48,
      "text": "but no more blood came from it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 784.54,
      "end": 784.8,
      "text": "and"
    },
    {
      "start": 785.08,
      "end": 788.1,
      "text": "all his long body was as still as the floor on which it lay."
    },
    {
      "start": 789.44,
      "end": 789.92,
      "text": "Spade said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 791.02,
      "end": 791.58,
      "text": "Lock the door.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 794.22,
      "end": 795.16,
      "text": "While Effie Perrine,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 795.4,
      "end": 796.36,
      "text": "her teeth chattering,"
    },
    {
      "start": 796.62,
      "end": 798.58,
      "text": "fumbled with the corridor door's lock,"
    },
    {
      "start": 799.136,
      "end": 800.7,
      "text": "Spade knelt beside the thin man,"
    },
    {
      "start": 800.94,
      "end": 802.4,
      "text": "turned him over on his back,"
    },
    {
      "start": 802.54,
      "end": 804.16,
      "text": "and ran a hand down inside his"
    },
    {
      "start": 804.22,
      "end": 804.58,
      "text": "overcoat."
    },
    {
      "start": 805.8,
      "end": 809.54,
      "text": "When he withdrew his hand presently it came out smeared with blood.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 810.44,
      "end": 811.0,
      "text": "The sight of",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 811.1,
      "end": 812.74,
      "text": "his bloody hand brought not the least"
    },
    {
      "start": 812.74,
      "end": 815.14,
      "text": "nor briefest of changes in Spade's face."
    },
    {
      "start": 817.12,
      "end": 819.06,
      "text": "Holding that hand up where it would touch nothing,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 819.58,
      "end": 821.5,
      "text": "he took his lighter out of his pocket with his"
    },
    {
      "start": 821.5,
      "end": 822.02,
      "text": "other hand."
    },
    {
      "start": 822.96,
      "end": 824.98,
      "text": "He snapped on the flame and held the flame",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 824.98,
      "end": 827.24,
      "text": "close to first one and then the other of"
    },
    {
      "start": 827.24,
      "end": 828.24,
      "text": "the thin man's eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 829.66,
      "end": 830.04,
      "text": "The eyes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 830.36,
      "end": 830.8,
      "text": "lids,"
    },
    {
      "start": 830.88,
      "end": 831.06,
      "text": "balls,"
    },
    {
      "start": 831.26,
      "end": 831.66,
      "text": "irises,"
    },
    {
      "start": 831.7,
      "end": 833.2,
      "text": "and pupils remained frozen,"
    },
    {
      "start": 833.6,
      "end": 834.18,
      "text": "immobile."
    },
    {
      "start": 835.584,
      "end": 838.7,
      "text": "Spade extinguished the flame and returned the lighter to his pocket.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 838.86,
      "end": 838.94,
      "text": "it."
    },
    {
      "start": 839.296,
      "end": 842.02,
      "text": "He moved on his knees around to the man's side,"
    },
    {
      "start": 842.2,
      "end": 844.04,
      "text": "and using his one clean hand,"
    },
    {
      "start": 844.28,
      "end": 844.93,
      "text": "unbuttoned"
    },
    {
      "start": 845.06,
      "end": 846.8,
      "text": "the tubular overcoat and opened it."
    },
    {
      "start": 847.94,
      "end": 850.26,
      "text": "The inside of the overcoat was wet with blood,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 850.5,
      "end": 851.24,
      "text": "and the"
    },
    {
      "start": 851.32,
      "end": 853.88,
      "text": "double-breasted blue jacket beneath it was sodden."
    },
    {
      "start": 854.86,
      "end": 855.92,
      "text": "The jacket's lapels,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 856.08,
      "end": 856.68,
      "text": "where they crossed"
    },
    {
      "start": 856.82,
      "end": 857.76,
      "text": "over the man's chest"
    },
    {
      "start": 858.3,
      "end": 861.16,
      "text": "and both sides of his coat immediately below that point,"
    },
    {
      "start": 861.34,
      "end": 862.02,
      "text": "were mangled"
    },
    {
      "start": 862.12,
      "end": 862.98,
      "text": "as if chewed."
    },
    {
      "start": 864.66,
      "end": 866.92,
      "text": "Spade rose and went to the wash-bowl in the outer office.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 868.256,
      "end": 868.88,
      "text": "Effie Perrine,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 869.12,
      "end": 871.16,
      "text": "wan and trembling and holding herself"
    },
    {
      "start": 871.16,
      "end": 873.08,
      "text": "upright by means of a hand and her"
    },
    {
      "start": 873.08,
      "end": 874.12,
      "text": "back against the door,"
    },
    {
      "start": 874.22,
      "end": 874.78,
      "text": "whispered,"
    },
    {
      "start": 875.68,
      "end": 876.96,
      "text": "\"'Is—is he—'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 877.8,
      "end": 878.1,
      "text": "\"'Yes.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 878.41,
      "end": 880.16,
      "text": "He's been shot through the chest,"
    },
    {
      "start": 880.36,
      "end": 882.09,
      "text": "maybe half a dozen times.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 883.168,
      "end": 884.74,
      "text": "Spade began to wash his hands.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 886.208,
      "end": 886.64,
      "text": "\"'Oughtn't we—'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 887.22,
      "end": 887.66,
      "text": "she began,"
    },
    {
      "start": 887.92,
      "end": 888.94,
      "text": "but he cut her short."
    },
    {
      "start": 890.3,
      "end": 891.64,
      "text": "It's too late for a doctor now,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 891.86,
      "end": 894.26,
      "text": "and I've got to think before we do anything.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 894.86,
      "end": 898.18,
      "text": "He finished washing his hands and began to rinse the bowl."
    },
    {
      "start": 899.08,
      "end": 901.42,
      "text": "He couldn't have gone far with those in him.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 902.3,
      "end": 904.82,
      "text": "If he—why in hell couldn't he have stood",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 904.82,
      "end": 906.38,
      "text": "up long enough to tell us something?"
    },
    {
      "start": 907.32,
      "end": 908.66,
      "text": "He frowned at the girl,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 908.82,
      "end": 909.94,
      "text": "rinsed his hands again,"
    },
    {
      "start": 910.06,
      "end": 911.08,
      "text": "and picked up a towel."
    },
    {
      "start": 912.44,
      "end": 913.18,
      "text": "\"'Pull yourself together.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 913.94,
      "end": 914.64,
      "text": "For God's sake,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 914.68,
      "end": 916.02,
      "text": "don't get sick on me now.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 916.64,
      "end": 919.24,
      "text": "He threw the towel down and ran fingers through his hair."
    },
    {
      "start": 920.64,
      "end": 921.89,
      "text": "We'll have a look at that bundle.\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 923.34,
      "end": 924.96,
      "text": "He went into the inner office again,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 925.12,
      "end": 926.88,
      "text": "stepped over the dead man's legs,"
    },
    {
      "start": 927.08,
      "end": 928.04,
      "text": "and picked up the"
    },
    {
      "start": 928.1,
      "end": 929.36,
      "text": "brown paper-wrapped parcel."
    },
    {
      "start": 930.1,
      "end": 932.58,
      "text": "When he felt its weight his eyes glowed.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 933.44,
      "end": 934.6,
      "text": "He put it on his desk,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 934.76,
      "end": 937.84,
      "text": "turning it over so that the knotted part of the rope was uppermost."
    },
    {
      "start": 938.82,
      "end": 939.68,
      "text": "The knot was hard",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 939.82,
      "end": 940.14,
      "text": "and tight."
    },
    {
      "start": 940.47,
      "end": 943.02,
      "text": "He took out his pocket-knife and cut the rope."
    },
    {
      "start": 944.38,
      "end": 945.52,
      "text": "The girl had left the door,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 945.7,
      "end": 948.28,
      "text": "and edging around the dead man with her face turned away,"
    },
    {
      "start": 948.5,
      "end": 948.8,
      "text": "had"
    },
    {
      "start": 949.04,
      "end": 950.04,
      "text": "come to Spade's side."
    },
    {
      "start": 951.2,
      "end": 952.04,
      "text": "As she stood there,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 952.18,
      "end": 954.16,
      "text": "with her hands on a corner of the desk,"
    },
    {
      "start": 954.36,
      "end": 955.04,
      "text": "watching him"
    },
    {
      "start": 955.04,
      "end": 957.48,
      "text": "pull the rope loose and push aside the brown paper,"
    },
    {
      "start": 957.74,
      "end": 960.88,
      "text": "excitement began to supplant nausea in her face."
    },
    {
      "start": 962.32,
      "end": 964.62,
      "text": "\"'Do you think it is?' she whispered.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 965.696,
      "end": 967.5,
      "text": "\"'We'll soon know,' Spade said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 967.68,
      "end": 971.58,
      "text": "his big fingers busy with the inner husk of coarse gray paper,"
    },
    {
      "start": 971.76,
      "end": 972.66,
      "text": "three sheets thick,"
    },
    {
      "start": 972.84,
      "end": 975.16,
      "text": "that the brown paper's removal had revealed."
    },
    {
      "start": 976.128,
      "end": 977.96,
      "text": "Though his face was hard and dull,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 978.22,
      "end": 979.32,
      "text": "his eyes were shining."
    },
    {
      "start": 981.2,
      "end": 983.22,
      "text": "When he had put the grey paper out of his way,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 983.38,
      "end": 984.88,
      "text": "he had an egg-shaped mass"
    },
    {
      "start": 984.88,
      "end": 986.74,
      "text": "of pale excelsior wadded tight."
    }
  ]
}